snippet: The resignation of the Palestinian Authority’s prime minister, Salam Fayyad, adds a layer of confusion to the already contentious Palestinian political scene.
abstract: Resignation of Salam Fayyad, internationally respected Palestinian politician and economist, as Palestinian Authority's prime minister leaves governmental body suspended in political ambiguity and confusion; departure could lead to Palestinian Authority's reconciliation with Hamas, causing problems in the West and possibly complicating peace efforts.

byline.contributor: Jodi Rudoren contributed reporting from Jerusalem, Khaled Abu Aker from Ramallah, West Bank, and Fares Akram from Gaza.

lead_paragraph: The resignation of the Palestinian Authority’s prime minister, Salam Fayyad, adds a layer of confusion to the already contentious Palestinian political scene.

headline.seo: Fayyad’s Resignation Means Uncertainty for Palestinians
headline.main: End of Palestinian Power Play Muddles the Peace Process
